description:
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Berkshire Foundation Trust is pleased to announce that following our recent CQC inspection we have maintained our rating of ‘&lt;strong&gt;Good’. &lt;/strong&gt;The CQC reported a strong patient-centred culture with a staff committed to keeping their patients safe and encouraging them to be independent. In return patients and relatives spoke highly of the staff and how they were informed of treatment plans, and how these would affect them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The trust provides a full range of outpatient services across different sites including Bracknell Healthspace, West Berkshire Community Hospital, Townlands Memorial Hospital and Royal Berkshire Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an Outpatient Manager to join the Integrated Medicine A team to support and develop the services delivered at all locations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Purpose of this role&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implementation of the Trust’s Outpatients Strategy and the ambition in the NHS long term plan&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead on standardising and centralising Outpatients processes and services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the development of new service plans and opportunities for the Trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Directors and teams across the Trust in implementing and delivering transformation and adopting new processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide leadership to colleagues through collaborative, visionary, motivational and problem solving approach&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As a senior leader and head of the service will be required to deal with difficult and occasionally contentious situations and matters; the post holder will show personal resilience and lead staff through difficulties in a positive way&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder has line management responsibilities for staff working in the service line, working closely with operational and clinical teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder ensures that the service line meet performance and financial targets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Horizon scan and actively generate new opportunities and partnerships for the Trust&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Director of Operations in strategic developments and projects, including the writing of bids for new services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advise executive team, non-executive directors and care groups leads on necessary service specific improvements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The post holder will be responsible for reporting performance outcomes, regularly evaluating against KPI’s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with stakeholders and develop new relationships in the Integrated Care Partnership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage the teams across all outpatient areas including satellite sites&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role would suit an individual who is passionate about delivering excellent patient care and looking for the next step in their career, or has had experience in a supervisory role in outpatients and has aspirations in developing their management experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
